                <head>No. 370.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Richmond</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-08-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 20, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 34.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No. 33,
                    giving particulars of the late disastrous earthquake on the island of
                    Ischia.</p>
                <p>The news of this calamity was very distressing to the President and to the people
                    of the United States, and you will kindly profit by an early opportunity to make
                    known to His Majesty’s Government the general deep sympathy with the relatives
                    of those who perished in the catastrophe, which prevails throughout this
                    country.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ALVEY A. ADEE,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
